blog.name: avenger-in-training-a
blog.title: I Can’t Help Avenge The Earth If Im Fat
blog.description: Star weight: 354 Goal weight: 165 Current Weight: 335 | Please note this is just my personal journey. I’m not trying to promote any way of living, or tell others how to live their lives. | Marvel and the Avengers Are the happiest part of my life, and telling myself I can’t be on their team until I’m fit is what motivates ME. It’s not for everyone. It’s probably dumb. But If it motivates me, it’s not dumb to me. |Anyway, my name is Alicia, I’m 23, and I just really wanna meet my goals.

summary: I’ve just decided what my ultimate reward for myself will be when I hit my goal weight.
body:
I’ve just decided what my ultimate reward for myself will be when I hit my goal weight.

When I hit my goal weight, which I know is going to take a few years of hard work…

I want to have a professional photo shoot done. The las time I had a professional photo shoot I was about 100 or so pounds lighter, and It was for my senor photo.

But this one will be special. I’ll actually make myself feel pretty and dressed up. OR Itll be a cosplay photo shoot. I loved Captain Marvel and would Look to look and feel good either cosplaying her or Black Widow.

I’m so excited and feelnextra motivated now.

I don’t know why being such a marvel nerd is helping me with this process, but I’m not even mad.

summary: Little spoiler for Infinite in which Grace’s Uncle Miguel tells her about the time he witnesses Captain Marvel’s encounter with...
caption:
Little spoiler for Infinite in which Grace’s Uncle Miguel tells her about the time he witnesses Captain Marvel’s encounter with a Skrull without him fully knowing just who she is. 

“I guess the weirdest thing I’ve ever seen was a woman get into a fight with an elderly lady on the metro line.”

“Really?”

“Yeah…it was super weird, but what was even more weird was the outfit the younger woman was wearing.”
